Paramedics were called out to the scene after several shots were fired. JOHANNESBURG - At least one person has been shot dead in Pietermaritzburg. Paramedics were called out to the scene after several shots were fired. Details are still sketchy but it’s believed the shooting is taxi-related. ER24's Russel Meiring says another person was wounded in the crime. “Assessments showed that the man had sustained numerous gunshot wounds and showed no signs of life. Unfortunately, nothing could be done for him and he was declared dead. “Further assessment showed that another man had sustained one gunshot wound to his leg. He was treated by paramedics and transported to the nearby provincial hospital for further care.” Police have been unavailable for comment. (Edited by Thapelo Lekabe)